### Telegram Bot API Tests
### REST Client extension required (humao.rest-client)
### Uses variables from .env file

@bot_token = {{$dotenv TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN}}
@chat_id = {{$dotenv TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID}}

### ========================================
### Bot Info
### ========================================

### Get Bot Info
GET https://api.telegram.org/bot{{bot_token}}/getMe
Accept: application/json

###

### Get Bot Commands
GET https://api.telegram.org/bot{{bot_token}}/getMyCommands
Accept: application/json

###

### ========================================
### Messages
### ========================================

### Send Test Message (Plain Text)
POST https://api.telegram.org/bot{{bot_token}}/sendMessage
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "chat_id": "{{chat_id}}",
  "text": "Test message from VS Code REST Client"
}

###

### Send Test Message (HTML)
POST https://api.telegram.org/bot{{bot_token}}/sendMessage
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "chat_id": "{{chat_id}}",
  "text": "<b>Test Alert</b>\n\nToken: <code>ABC123</code>\nScore: 85/100",
  "parse_mode": "HTML"
}

###

### Send Test Alert (Full Format)
POST https://api.telegram.org/bot{{bot_token}}/sendMessage
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "chat_id": "{{chat_id}}",
  "text": "NEW TOKEN ALERT\n\n$TEST (Test Token)\nCA: AbC123...xyz\n\nLiquidity: $10,000\nHolders: 150\nRisk Score: 75/100\n\nSafety: LP Burned\nMint Auth: Revoked\n\nDexScreener | Birdeye",
  "parse_mode": "HTML",
  "disable_web_page_preview": true
}

###

### ========================================
### Updates
### ========================================

### Get Updates (Check for incoming messages)
GET https://api.telegram.org/bot{{bot_token}}/getUpdates
Accept: application/json

###

### Get Updates with Offset
GET https://api.telegram.org/bot{{bot_token}}/getUpdates?offset=-1&limit=10
Accept: application/json

###

### ========================================
### Webhook (if using)
### ========================================

### Get Webhook Info
GET https://api.telegram.org/bot{{bot_token}}/getWebhookInfo
Accept: application/json

###

### Delete Webhook (to use polling instead)
POST https://api.telegram.org/bot{{bot_token}}/deleteWebhook
Content-Type: application/json

{}

